@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy";
}

<section class="hero-panel hero-panel-compact">
    <span class="eyebrow">Privacy And Security</span>
    <h1>Why this example is safe for classroom use.</h1>
    <p class="lead mb-0">
        The project runs locally, stores data in memory for the current session only, and uses no external services or secrets.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="card-grid">
    <article class="info-card">
        <h2>Data Handling</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Tasks disappear when the app stops because they are not written to a database.</li>
            <li>No personal student data is required to run the demo.</li>
            <li>All requests stay inside the local ASP.NET Core application.</li>
        </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="info-card">
        <h2>CORS Note</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>A development CORS policy is registered in <code>Program.cs</code>.</li>
            <li>This prepares students for later examples where frontend and backend use different ports.</li>
            <li>For this project, requests are same-origin, so no extra browser setup is required.</li>
        </ul>
    </article>
</section>
